    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely\u00a0dice the <strong>brown\u00a0onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail and finely dice\u00a0the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion and carrots are cooking, peel and finely slice\u00a0(don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong>\u00a0pork & beef rag\u00f9 mince\u00a0</strong>and cook for 3-4 min further, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes are starting to break down</p><p>Tip: Crush the tomatoes with a wooden spoon as you stir</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong>\u00a0beef stock mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and<strong>\u00a0tomato paste</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span><strong> milk</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> stock</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes have started to break down, add the <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 15-20 min or until the sauce has thickened to a rich, bolognese-like consistency \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>Bolognese rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the Bolognese rag\u00f9 has been cooking for 5-10 min, add the <strong>pappardelle </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until tender with a slight bite (this is known as al dent\u00e9)</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pappardelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pick the smaller leaves from the <strong>basil</strong> and set them aside for garnish</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Stir the <strong>drained pappardelle </strong>and<strong> chopped basil</strong>\u00a0through the <strong>Bolognese rag\u00f9</strong>\u00a0and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>Bolognese rag\u00f9 with pappardelle </strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-with-pappardelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Bolognese rag\u00f9 with pappardelle</strong>\u00a0and garnish with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>reserved\u00a0basil leaves</strong></p><p>Season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Buon appetito!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
